Name: Meckel syndrome 1
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of MKS1 on chromosome 17q22.

Name: Meckel syndrome 2
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of TMEM216 on chromosome 11q12.2.

Name: Meckel syndrome 3
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of TMEM67 on chromosome 8q22.1.

Name: Meckel syndrome 4
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of CEP290 on chromosome 12q21.32.

Name: Meckel syndrome 5
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of RPGRIP1L on chromosome 16q12.2.

Name: Meckel syndrome 6
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of CC2D2A on chromosome 4p15.32.

Name: Meckel syndrome 7
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of NPHP3 on chromosome 3q22.1.

Name: Meckel syndrome 8
Definition: A Meckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of TCTN2 on chromosome 12q24.31.

Name: Meckel syndrome 13
Definition: An autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the RUN and SH3 domain containing 2 gene (RUSC2) on chromosome 9p13.
